  "prompt": "The Last Man on Earth (TV series): Where did all the dead bodies go on The Last Man on Earth?",
  "response": "In the TV series \"The Last Man on Earth,\" the massive die-off from the virus left countless dead bodies everywhere initially. However, as the series progressed, most of the bodies seemed to disappear or were not prominently shown. This was likely a practical production decision to make the post-apocalyptic world more visually palatable and less disturbing.\n\nThe show never provided a definitive explanation for the disappearance of the bodies. Possible implied or suggested reasons could include:\n- Natural decomposition over time\n- Animals and scavengers breaking down remains\n- Some off-screen cleanup by survivors\n- Creative choice by the writers to avoid constantly showing gruesome scenes\n\nThe series focused more on the characters' survival and interactions rather than dwelling on the logistical details of the massive population loss. The vanishing bodies were essentially a narrative convenience that allowed the show to concentrate on the comedy and drama of the characters' post-apocalyptic existence.",
